
[1]scrofulous

   SCROF'ULOUS, a.

   1. Pertaining to scrofula, or partaking of its nature; as scrofulous
   tumors; a scrofulous habit of body.

   2. Diseased or affected with scrofula.

   Scrofulous persons can never be duly nourished.
